3. **`<;> rfl`**: After simplification, both sides of the equality are the same (`g`), so `rfl` proves the remaining goal by reflexivity.

This completes the proof that `homF (id X)` is the identity function on `Hom X c`, as required by the `map_id` axiom for contravariant functors. 

